parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Winntec propane regulator can cause an increase in propane pressure, leading to a larger flame, and potentially igniting adjacent materials, resulting in a fire or explosion.
symptoms: propane tank filling up with fuel
front burner of the stove throwing a flame far back to the microwave
rear burner not having enough pressure to light the stove when low on propane.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for the recall repair can cause a delay in fixing the issue, potentially leading to accidents or fires due to the faulty propane regulator.
symptoms: Parts not available for recall repair
owners unable to use their RVs due to safety concerns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Insufficient greasing of wheel bearings can cause premature wear, heat stress, and eventual failure, leading to wheel wobbling, vibration, and potentially, accidents or fires.
symptoms: wheel bearings overheating and welding together.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Weld failure in suspension components can cause the axle to shift, leading to wheel bearings overheating, and potentially, accidents or fires.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Inspection and Quality Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of inspection and quality control can lead to undetected issues, such as insufficient greasing of wheel bearings and weld failures, which can cause accidents or fires.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Trailer Hitch and Body Flexing Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive body flexing and moving front cap can cause the sides to detach from the front trim molding, potentially leading to trailer damage or loss while towing, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The front cap appears to be moving or shifting
the sides of the trailer come out of the front trim molding
unusual noises or vibrations while towing.
